        <h2>Simple planning tools for outdoor projects</h2>
        <p>Backyard Math was created to help homeowners, DIYers, gardeners, and weekend project planners estimate materials for common outdoor projects.</p>
        <p>Whether you are planning a fire pit, building raised garden beds, installing a patio, spreading mulch, ordering gravel, filling low spots with topsoil, or estimating concrete, these tools are designed to give you a quick starting point before you buy materials.</p>
        <p>The goal is simple: help you spend less time doing math and more time making progress on your project.</p>

        <h2>How the calculators work</h2>
        <p>The calculators use standard area, volume, coverage, and unit conversion formulas. Many tools also include optional overage to account for waste, uneven ground, settling, breakage, cuts, and measuring differences.</p>
        <p>For the most accurate estimate, always use your actual project measurements and product specifications from your local supplier.</p>

        <h2>Important note</h2>
        <p>Backyard Math provides estimates for planning purposes only. The calculators are not a substitute for professional advice, engineering guidance, local code requirements, product instructions, or contractor recommendations.</p>

